Two people have been confirmed dead and over a thousand injured when two trains collided at the Mountain view train station in Pretoria West. The incident occurred after nine o’clock on Tuesday morning.  The cause of the crash is still unknown. It’s a chaotic scene outside the Mountain view train station as paramedics rush those who have been seriously injured to various hospitals around the city. The death toll remains at two but emergency services personnel say it might rise to four. Buses have been arranged to transport those who survived the crash.